The '''Guild of Zygerrian Slavers''' was one of the larger [[slaver guild]]s in operation during the reign of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. It was based on the [[Slavery/Legends|slave trade]] [[Planet/Legends|world]] of [[Zygerria/Legends|Zygerria]].

==History==
[[File:Zygerrian.jpg|thumb|left|150px|A Zygerrian slaver]]
The guild began its operations during the time of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. In the era of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], their size and structure made it beneficial for the Empire to offer [[slaver permit]]s at a reduced cost. They trafficked mainly in [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'leks]] and native [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorians]]. [[Terrinald Screed/Legends|Terrinald Screed]] personally vouched for the quality of their Twi'leks. The Guild also occasionally dealt in [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]], but were unable to break the monopoly the [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshans]] had in the [[Kashyyyk system/Legends|Kashyyyk system]].

With the rise of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], the Zygerrian Slavers Guild became a remnant of its former power as the new galactic government outlawed slavery. Despite this, the practice still continued in criminal havens, and the Zygerrians continued to supply slaves to [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] [[Kajidic/Legends|crime families]] and other similar groups.<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref>

